title.jp: Mogitate Fresh! Cure Peach Tanjou!!

synopsis: The fairy elder goes to Pretty Cure Forest and prays in the corresponding temple. Lightning strikes the temple and the elder sees four Pickruns flying away. Meanwhile, in the human world, Love goes to the dance unit Trinity event. On the way, a huge monster called a Nakewameke appears, ruining the event. Love tries to protect her idol, Miyuki. Suddenly, the Pirun appears and goes to her mobile phone, transforming her into Cure Peach and allowing her to battle the monster.

title.jp: Tsumitate Fresh! Cure Berry Tanjou!!

synopsis: After the battle, Tart appears in front of Love. According to Tart, she is the legendary warrior, Precure, who has to stop Mobius' ambition. Love is shocked upon hearing this. Tart tells Love that they need to find the other three Precure. Meanwhile, Miki encounters a vending machine-like Nakewameke, and transforms into Cure Berry through the use of the Blun to protect her brother.

title.jp: Toretate Fresh! Cure Pine Tanjou!!

synopsis: Inori has begun feeling a bit left out because she is too shy to dance with Love and Miki. She finds comfort in taking care of a little boy's dog. When the dog becomes a Nakewameke, Inori gains the ability to transform into Cure Pine through the Kirun.

title.jp: Chiffon ga Maigo? Machijuu Mou Oosawagi!!

synopsis: Chiffon goes missing and causes a lot of trouble in town, it's up to the girls to find her.

title.jp: Yuuenchi de DokiDoki! Wakuwaku Date Kibun!?

synopsis: Three boys from Love's school go on a triple date with the girls. Wester makes a panda cart become a Nakewameke and causes chaos, that is unless the girls stop him.

title.jp: Kieta Hamburger! Daisuki na Mono wo Mamore!!

synopsis: Love buys hamburgers at the shop where her mother works. After Love finishes cooking the hamburgers disappear due to Souler's Nakewameke. Later on, the same Nakewameke erases the Cures' mothers, and it is up to the Cures to finish off the Nakewameke.

title.jp: Setsuna to Love, Yuujou no Clover!

synopsis: Setsuna goes to the town centre to meet Love according to fortune telling. Love is playing Lucky Draw in town when Setsuna meets her. She asked Love to give a tour of the town, on the way, she tries to steal Love's Linkrun.

title.jp: Chiffon Dai Pinch! Peach no Atarashii Chikara!!

synopsis: Love accidentally forgot to refil the Cure Vitan, Chiffon's food, and lost the contact to get more. Chiffon cannot get food from Linkrun, so Love has to cook something for Chiffon. Cure Peach's new weapon, the Peach Rod, first appears in this episode.

title.jp: Miki no Yume, Watashi Precure Yameru!!

synopsis: Miki wants to be a famous top model around the world. One day she got the chance for the audition; if she passes the audition, she can get the chance to be a model overseas. She is very happy, but at the same time, she thinks of Love and Inori, because if she passes, she has to say farewell to them. She is puzzled when she realizes that she has to quit dance and Pretty Cure in order to fulfill her dream.

title.jp: Tart ga Inori de Inori ga Tart!?

synopsis: Inori is afraid of ferrets, so she dare not to approach Tart. One day, from Souler's Nakewameke they swap bodies and it is up to the girls to stop him.

title.jp: Miyuki no Ikari! Mou Dance wa Oshienai!?

synopsis: The girls come late to a dance session. Miyuki gets angry at this and she won't teach the girls dancing anymore.

title.jp: Minna de Henshin! Fusafusa Daisakusen!!

synopsis: Wester turns one of Love's dad's wigs into a Nakewameke, which gives everyone in Clover Town Street weird hairstyles.instead of what westar's wished,the children is happy,though.

title.jp: Chiffon ga Byouki!? Pine no Atarashii Chikara!!

synopsis: When Chiffon falls ill, Inori is tasked with nursing her back to health. Cure Pine's new weapon, the Pine Flute, makes its debut.

title.jp: Yoninme no Pretty Cure!? Akarun wo Sagase!!

synopsis: Now that Chiffon is able to talk, she tells of four special Pickruns. These give the girls the ability to become Pretty Cure and grant them powers. Three of them, the Pirun, the Blun, and the Kirun, are found. All that remains is the Akarun, a red Pickrun...

title.jp: Setsuna to Love, Aite wo Omoiyaru Kokoro!

synopsis: Love meets with Setsuna once again. Setsuna learns that Love truly trusts her as a friend.

title.jp: Kyoufu no Bunkasai! Yoru no Gakkou ni Hibiku Ashioto!!

synopsis: It's time for the Culture Festival in Love's school. Love and Daisuke has a fight during school. When Love gets trapped inside the school with Daisuke, they have to work together to escape the Nakewameke.

title.jp: Chiffon wa Makasete! Berry no Atarashii Chikara!!

synopsis: Miki is tasked with babysitting Chiffon. Cure Berry's new weapon, the Berry Sword, makes it first appearance.

title.jp: Precure ni Aitai! Chiisana Onnanoko no Negai!!

synopsis: Love and the girls meet a terminally ill girl in a hospital. Having seen Pretty Cure before, the sick girl wishes to meet them.

title.jp: Aratana Card! Eas no Atarashii Chikara!!

synopsis: Mobius, the being running Labyrinth, sees that it's time to destroy Pretty Cure. He gives Eas a new card, but the card has bad side effects to the user...

title.jp: Dance to Precure... Dochira wo Erabu?

synopsis: Due to all the training for a dance competition, the girls are worn out and are being slowed down. They have to choose whether to keep dancing or live on being just Pretty Cure.

title.jp: Yoninme no Precure wa Ansan ya!!

synopsis: The night before the dance competition, the girls are hospitalized due to fatigue. Miyuki realizes that while it's important to focus on dance, it's also important to focus on recovery. She soon finds about Pretty Cure, but refuses to become the red Cure.

title.jp: Setsuna to Love, Anata ga Eas nano!?

synopsis: After being discharged, the girls believe that Miyuki is the fourth member of Pretty Cure. They go on another search for the Akarun. However, they run into Eas again, who reveals her identity as Setsuna.

title.jp: Eas no Saigo! Cure Passion Tanjou!!

synopsis: Setsuna is purified by Cure Peach and becomes something she'd never thought she would become: the red Cure of happiness, Cure Passion.

title.jp: Setsuna no Kunou, Watashi wa Nakama ni Narenai!

synopsis: Setsuna, who has just become Cure Passion, doesn't have a place to go back to. While she's walking down the street, she meets Love, who's going to a restaurant with her parents.

title.jp: Eas tai Passion!? Watashi wa Umarekawaru!!

synopsis: Setsuna is haunted by her past deeds as Eas and must confront them when a doppelganger of Eas attacks the Pretty Cures.

title.jp: Yottsu no Heart! Watashi mo Odoritai!!

synopsis: Setsuna feels that she wants to join Clover, the dancing group formed by Love, Miki, and Inori.

title.jp: Natsu da! Matsuri da! Audrey!!

synopsis: During the summer festival, the girls meet a comedy duo called Audrey.

title.jp: Taisetsu na Kioku! Ojii-chan to no Omoide!!

synopsis: Remembering the time spent with her grandfather, a Nakewameke causes Love to dream of being reunited with him. However, Love must choose between staying with her grandfather in this dream world or helping her friends defeat the Nakewameke.

title.jp: Nazo Darake no Otoko! Kaoru-chan no Shoutai!?

synopsis: The girls and Tart begin to realize something is up with Kaoru and they investigate.

title.jp: Tart Kikiippatsu! Shoutai ga Barechau!?

synopsis: One day, Tart starts having stomachaches. Ayumi, Love's Mother, brings him to Dr. Yamabuki's, not knowing Tart is actually a fairy from the Sweets Kingdom!

title.jp: Love to Daisuke, Nakanaori no Shikata!

synopsis: The new school term has begun. Love is happy seeing that Setsuna has become popular in Yotsuba Junior High, but Daisuke isn't happy...

title.jp: Sayonara! Tart to Chiffon!!

synopsis: Tart and Chiffon return to the Sweets Kingdom, and the Cures have accompanied them. That, and they find out Tart is the Prince of the Kingdom and is engaged to a pink ferret named Azukiina. The Clover music box of Happiness debuts in this episode.

title.jp: Miki to Setsuna no Kowai Mono!

synopsis: Miki has trouble fighting an octopus Nakewameke, because she has a fear of octopuses.

title.jp: Infiniti Arawareru! Ashita wo Torimodose!!

synopsis: The treasure Infinity makes its appearance, a new villain arrives to aid Moebius, and a whole day gets replayed over and over.

title.jp: Chiffon no Kakusareta Himitsu!

synopsis: Chiffon is apparently more powerful than she appears to be like making herself a pickrun,giving the cures a boost of power,and more!

title.jp: Aratana Teki! Sono Na wa Northa!!

synopsis: The new enemy Northa appears in this episode.

title.jp: Chiffon wo Mamore! Precure no Atarashii Chikara!!

synopsis: Pretty Cure get intense training from Miyuki, and Chiffon grants them a new power: the group attack, Lucky Clover Grand Finale.

title.jp: Clover Box wo Sagase!!

synopsis: Miki loses the Clover music box by accident and now she must protect it from Labyrinth's hands.

title.jp: Kenka wa Kinshi? Okinawa Shuugaku Ryokou!!

synopsis: Love and Setsuna go to Okinawa on a research trip together with their classmates.

title.jp: Setsuna to Love, Okaasan ga Abunai!

synopsis: Setsuna suspects that something is wrong with Love's mother, Ayumi, and discovers that Love's "mother" was a Sorewaatase clone of the real one.

title.jp: Inori to Kento no Senjou Party!

synopsis: Kento invites Inori to a boat party on a ship.

title.jp: Labyrinth kara no Shoutaijou!

synopsis: Setsuna is hostage by Northa ,and it's up to her friends to rescue her from being brainwashed back into Labyrinth!

title.jp: Sekai wo Sukue! Precure tai Labyrinth!!

synopsis: The Pretty Cures enter into labyrinth's base in order to destroy the 'fuko gage' as they are fighting against Northa and her tricks.

title.jp: Ayashiki Kusabue! Ubawareta Chiffon!!

synopsis: Northa comes up with a plan to kidnap Chiffon by distracting Pretty Cure.

title.jp: Yonin wa Precure! Christmas Eve no Wakare!!

synopsis: Love and her friends decide to save Chiffon but they will have to reveal their identities as Pretty Cure in front of their parents and friends.

title.jp: Souler to Wester, Saigo no Tatakai!!

synopsis: Moebius sends Souler and Wester to defeat Pretty Cure without them knowing that he had something else in mind. Note: This was the first Pretty Cure episode to air in the 2010s.

title.jp: Sekai ga Kawaru! Donuts ga Okoshita Kiseki!!

synopsis: The denizens of Labyrinth were changed by Tart, Azukina and...donuts!

title.jp: Saishuu Kessen! Cure Angels Tanjou!!

synopsis: Things seemed hopeless for Pretty Cure until two new heroes and the people of Labyrinth came to help them.

title.jp: Odoroki no Shinjitsu! Moebius no Hontou no Sugata!!

synopsis: Moebius isn't what he seems to be...

title.jp: Egao ga Ippai! Minna de Shiawase Get da yo!!

synopsis: The final battle between Cure Angel and Moebius. Will Pretty Cure be able to save Chiffon and the parallel worlds in time? Anyway, Love, Miki, Inori and Setsuna toward to face for the new future. But, what will happen to Tsubomi and Erika...
